"Yeah, kids grow up so quickly"
'Can't believe he grew up so quick'

"We will probably just spend most of the time here at home, no big plans really."
'What do you usually do when he visits?'

"You're only as old as you feel is what I say."
'I understand. I think we will do the same. I hope he brings a few of his friends. I am not that old... if you know what I mean :)'

'Not really since I am usually spending my time alone in my studio painting, but I might give it some thought.'
"Yes, that's exactly right! If you don't mind me asking, have you ever considered any of your son's friends? ^_^"

'Well everyone is an adult so who am I to judge, sounds like a good bit of fun to me.'
'You should. I am not really a blond, but I would say cute and the kids dig me. :) And you know, sometimes I let them play with me'

'Just about to clean up my paints and and put them away for the day.'
'What are you up to now, girl?'

Canning is great for storing food. Sometimes I can food before my marathons to calm my anxiety.
Wow, you've done a marathon?  I run a bit, but never tried anything long

Yeah it's a great way to keep your heart healthy! I wish the marathons were in the evening though. Are you a morning or night person?
I'm totally a morning person.  I wake naturally around 6 a.m. And you?

I wake up at 6 a.m.when I have work, sometimes I'll get up at 5 a.m. though for a morning run.
So, how long and how far is your morning run?  And when you prepare for a marathon?

Generally I'll run about 3 miles, but when a marathon is coming up I'll build my way up to 5 or 7 miles every morning.
That's impressive.  I would like to try but I just don't have the stamina! Do you ever run with a dog?

I don't have a dog, I just don't have the time to dedicate to a pet! Do you have any pets?
No pets, just a crowd of feral cats from the neighborhood that roam through the yard. Fun to watch.

Oh that sounds funny, I like seeing cats roaming about the neighborhood. Cats are quiet creatures that really know how to take it easy!
We've had to step in a few times when one was injured, or a mama cat died. But they are timid creatures.

I would suggest a fitness place with a rock wall. Try that out in a safe environment

I will do that. I will take my mom with me since she is my best friend.
It's good to have a spotter! Also, get in overall good shape with an emphasis on balance

Where should be go after the fitnes place? Would the ocean be a good spot?
Ha ha - not for rock climbing. Maybe you are thinking of diving?

I was thinking about diving. I would love to see some real life mermaids.
You may need to limit yourself to Disneyland for mermaids. They're not actually real.

Thats not true. My mother told me they really exist.
I see. I wonder where she has seen them?

She saw them when she was younger. I will believe my best friend since I know my mother well.
Far be it to argue with anyone's mother! Do you have siblings?

"Pets are part of the family like humans, what type of pets do you have if any"
"I have one cat but I want to get another! Do you have any pets?"
"They are a cross of a poodle and golden retriever, they make great family dogs, kids love them"
"Wow, I've never heard of goldendoodles before. That's a bit hard to pronounce with my accent!"
"Cats can be picky if you do get one get a puppy so they get along"

"What do your kids look back at the pictures you kept of them over the years"
"Usually pictures of their families and their pets that they love so much."
"I do, I have a family member who has an adorable ragdoll cat named Max"
"That sounds so cute. My kitty could really use a friend, maybe I'll get a goldendoodle!"
"That's a smart idea, I want my kitty to feel at home. Do you like cats?"
"Kids can be picky if you do get one get a puppy so they get along"

مال من سبز است.

آیا این زمان سال را دوست دارید؟ من تغییر فصل‌ها را دوست دارم اما خیلی علاقه‌ای به هوای سرد زمستان ندارم.

زمستان ممکن است طولانی به نظر برسد، من فقط سعی می‌کنم به یاد داشته باشم که فصل بعدی بهار است، من بهار را دوست دارم، هوا در اواخر بهار عالی است.

من به بسیاری از شهرها در سراسر جهان سفر کرده‌ام، سعی کنید از شهرهایی که فصل بارانی دارند یا در زمستان خیلی سرد می‌شوند، پرهیز کنید.

بله برخی شهرها، مانند ونیز در زمستان غرق می‌شوند یا بسیار سرد می‌شوند مانند شهرهای شمالی در اروپا، آمریکا و کانادا.

این یک راه خوب برای یافتن یک پرواز یا هتل ارزان است، اما بخاطر من هم مناسب نیست.

"I am surprised how many reality tv shows are on air, what's your favorite type"

"I like the outdoors type, the ones based in Alaska are interesting"
"i have seen cop shows based in alaska, there's a lot of socioeconomic issues up there"

"I think like many reality shows they exaggerate how bad things are for ratings"
"yeah, for sure. they make their own narrative to make a more interesting watching experience"

"Some of the home improvement reality shows are interesting but they make their job look easier than it is"
"it looks easy when they can condense months of work into 30 minute - 1 hour episodes"

"that's true, I wish they would show more of the work it takes to get a project started and completed"
"i do understand that it makes for better watching to have a really drastic before and after shot without all the gritty work details"

"Yes! Time especially goes by fast when I'm working at my job. I'm constantly busy."
"So true! We just had a baby, and work just flies by! I usually can't wait to get back home."

"I understand that. I have a 5 year old so I'm anxious to get back home and enjoy time with him."
"Do you just have the one kid? This is my first."

"Yes, I just have one kid. I'm hoping to start trying for another within the next year or two."
"My wife want to start trying now. Seems like so much is happening quickly."

"Oh that's exciting! How many more do you all want? I want just 1 more. I'd love to have a girl this time."
"We want to have at least 6 kids. We are from Italy, and we love having big families!"

"Oh, that is awesome! Do you and your wife come from a big family?"
"My wife does, I am an only child. My mom is in the medical field and did not really have time for kids."

"I'm an only child as well. I wish that I had siblings growing up but it did allow me special moments with my parents."
"I do not see my mom much, but I have a great relationship with my dad."

"I'm a thrill seaker. Do you like extreme sports?"
"I usually don't. But this one was very impressive."

"What do you like most about it?"
"I really like just being able to escape to a different world."

"Yeah, like everything fades away. Do you ever watch the olympics?"
"I usually don't, but I do enjoy watching it during the summer Olympics!"

"What is your favorite olympic sport?"
"I like swimming. What's yours?"

"Summer sport would be skateboarding, and winter would be ice cross."
"That's cool. What got you into watching sports?"

"Acess to the tv, lol. Just kidding. I love to participate so watching was a way to learn more about the sports I like. What about you."
"Mostly just lack of anything else to do around here, and all my friends were into sports at the time"

"I completely agree. It makes you realize how important it is to spend time with people while they are here."
"Absolutely, it's a chapter of your life and as long as you have those memories they live on through those memories."

"That is a really good way of looking at it. And you can share those memories with new people in your life and breathe life into them."
"You are so right. It can make all the difference."

"Do you have other family members to help you after your loss?"
"yeah we have a large close knit family. how bout you?"

"We keep in touch, but all my immediate family lives rather far. So it is just me and my dogs at home."
"same here . i just know a lot of people that actually is going through it ."

من متوجهم. حتی اگر اجباری بود، خوشحالم که آن را گرفتم زیرا به نظر می‌رسد نیاز داشتم که به دلیل داشتن تجربه در دوره انتخابات سیاسی در سال ۲۰۰۴.

آره، این همون دلیلی بود که من به دانشگاه برای سخت‌افزار کامپیوتر رفتم، در صورتی که مسئله سیاسی شکست خورد. من اکنون کامپیوترهای خودم را ساخته و فروشگاه خودم را اداره می‌کنم.

اوه اما من انجام دادم، در واقع من معاون رئیس جمهور این کشور واقعیت‌پرداز هستم

این به نام لیگما است، من هفته ای حدود ۸۰۰ هزار دلار درآمد دارم

"It's amazing how a little kindness from strangers can go such a long way."
"He thought I was cute and old fashioned since I wore a locket. I still love to line dry my clothes! Nothing better, I say!"
"I agree with you! The way linens smell after being air dried is way better than any dryer sheet"
"A word of advice, always hang your clothes higher than your goats can reach! I learned that early on living on a homestead! Explains the missing socks!"
"Oh wow yeah! I never thought about that. I don't raise animals but my neighbor does. I do like to hunt deer from time to time."
"We've had so many animals but their all for slaughter or use on the farm, chickens for eggs, goats for milk, ya know.... we hunt a lot as well."
"That's great. I love animals, but I also love the thrill of the hunt. I use a bow to make it more interesting."
"Wow! A bow! You're a true hunter! Ya know, all these animals I've owned but I've never had a true indoor pet?"
"Really? Man, pets are great too. I am lost without my dog."
"I'll one day own a ferret. I've been selling our extra eggs at the market to save up for one!"
"Keep at it! Ferrets are cute little things. Where would you put it?"
"I'd cage it at night but take it with me during the day. Ferrets are canines so you can train them like dogs."

"اوه واقعاً! من هرگز به این فکر نکرده بودم. من حیوانات نمی‌پرورانم اما همسایه‌ام انجام می‌دهد. من از زمان به زمان دوست دارم گوزن شکار کنم."

این عالیه. من عاشق حیوانات هستم، اما همچنین از هیجان شکار لذت می‌برم. من از کمان استفاده می‌کنم تا شکار جذاب‌تر شود.

یک نکته، همیشه لباس‌هایتان را بالاتر از اینکه بزهایتان بتوانند برسند آویزان کنید! من این را زودی یاد گرفتم زندگی در یک مزرعه! این موضوع گم شدن جوراب‌ها را توضیح می‌دهد!

"I really like listening to Imagine Dragons while I work in the garden. It's my favorite thing to do."
"I will try and see them on tour."

"They are awesome! I took my grandkids to a live concert of theirs. They laughed when they saw their old Pops getting down to their generation's music."
"haaa, nice. how did you first hear about Imagine Dragons?"

"It was an accident, actually. I'm a big fantasy novel reader and was Googling dragons to find a new book and they came up on my search."
"cool. I'm a big fan of Sci-fi. how many grand children do you have?"

"I have 4, all boys! The eldest got married last spring and are expecting! This old man is about to be a great grandpa!"
"awesome. Have you thought about buying a RV to visit all of them?"

"I have. I'd go travel in winter when I don't have the garden to tend to."
"nice. Yes, I am considering buying a Van."

"You can get some awesome vans now that you can practically live in. The minimalist movement has really paved a way for that lifestyle."
"yes, I've heard of Radioactive. listen to music while running"

جالبه، ممنون که به من اطلاع دادی. همچنین، شاید بتوانند به نحوی تلفن را خودکار خاموش کنند هنگام رانندگی.

"Yeah, I actually don't watch a lot of baseball, but I try to follow the world series a little."
"I watch a lot of baseball but i play basketball more often. in fact I am currently training with my personal coach"

"Cool, do you play professionally? Or are you trying to make a career out of it?"
"I was an avid runner in high school and found my interest in basketball in college. I am training to make it a career now. How about you? "

"I am in the automotive sales business. I source cars for a large business."
"i see, how did you find your interest in auto?"

"I have just always loved cars since a young age. I love talking about cars with people, and advising them on which ones are good to buy."
"I am looking for a vehicle currently. Any suggestions?"

"Toyota and Honda makes the most reliable cars, hands down. Corollas and Camrys run forever. Stay away from German cars."
"why do you say that"

"I very consistently see Toyotas with over 200k miles. I see a lot of German cars that have issues before they even hit 100k, plus they depreciate heavily."
"ohhhh okay that makes more sense"

'We could never have to many registered nurses'
'There will always be sick people. '

"Aren't you worried about getting sick yourself?"
'Not really. we take precausions to prevent that. Besides, sick people need someone who wants to be with them no matter what they have.'

'Does that require you to be away from your spouse for long periods of time?'
'Yes. Espeacially if you work at a hospital'

'How would one try to become an RN'
'There are courses for it at most colleges. Takes two to four years to get, but if you love helping people, then it is worth it.'

'I would really love to join a part of the medical field, all it takes is dedication and hard work to achieve anything!'
'That is so true. If more people would realize their potential the world would be so much better'

"I couldn't agree with you more."
'Too many people are lazy and look for the easy way though'

"I'm sorry to hear that.  Why are you insecure?"
"I am not insecure."
"Which do you prefer, selling houses or waitressing?"
"I like selling houses more because I don't have to interact with lots of people."
"You prefer the one on one relationships.  I can understand that.  Have you been selling houses a long time?"
"Exactly. I have been selling houses since I was 12 years old!"
"Really!  That is impressive.  What kinds of houses?"
"mostly larger houses that celebrities buy. I sold one once for $10 million."
"How were you able to sell houses when you ere 12?"
"Well it wasn't just me, my parents helped me through the process. But my name was on the sign!"
"That's impressive.  How many years have you been selling houses?"
"Well I'm 100 now so about 88 years!"
"I think you are Joking but it's been fun chatting"
"I was hehe. great chatting with you"

چطور می‌دانی چنین چیزهایی؟

این یکی خوبه! من شخصاً یک پیشخدمت هستم.

مطمئنم که زیادی از مردم در فروشگاه مواد غذایی از شما می‌خواهند که به چیزهایی که روی قفسه بالا هستند دسترسی پیدا کنید.

بله، این خیلی منطقی است. پدر و مادر من قد متوسطی دارند و من هم همینطور، ههه.

آیا تا به حال خارج از کشور بوده‌اید؟ احتمالاً به زودی قصد دارم به استرالیا بروم تا با شریک زندگی‌ام ازدواج کنم.

من هم ندارم. من هیجان زده هستم، اما همچنین خیلی عصبانی.

You can actually count cards to make an informed guess, but it is usually frowned upon in casinos.
I don't have the best of luck at casinos.

Yes, I am a dealer in a casino, and I can say that it takes tons of practice.
Do you have to have a special talent to be a dealer?

No, not really. You can generally learn the skills on the job while being trained, but it helps to be outgoing.
Is it fun learning to become a dealer?

Yes, I love it. Plus you can make really good tip money if you like to talk to people.
Do dealers encounter many issues with players?

Sometimes. It usually is due to people being intoxicated, but security is usually pretty good about taking over in those issues.
It seem like becoming a dealer would be a fun job to pursue, I would love to learn to become a dealer.

I would definitely recommend it. It is relatively easy, and a lot of fun.
Thanks so much for the information.

I like those too, and also fiction. Some authors are good mixing fiction with real places and people, those are my favorite.
Yeah, I definitely see the appeal with fiction. Reading is an escape for some people!

To me reading is a need. But is not my only hobby, I also love sports and music.

I love soccer and swimming, and things that you can do with a lot of friends, hiking too. And do you have a favorite sport?

"Great. What are you doing today?"

"That's a good idea, I should start preparing for winter as well."
"Yeah. This summer was so hot!!!!!!!!! I am hoping for a chilly fall and frigid winter!!!"

"I agree! I'm excited to see what winter brings into the area."
"I'm sure we are going to get pounded with snow. Gotta watch out for the black ice!!!"

"Yes! I'd better get to the store soon to pick up some salt. When do you guys normally start seeing snow around here?"
"Usually in December but with climate change we could get a November blizzard!"

"Yes. I can't believe he would do this knowing what I'm going through with the divorce!"
"Yeah, well, my big brother once hit me in the head with the claw end of a hammer."

"What a jerk! If I was there I could've helped you, since I'm in my second year of medical school."
"Ha-ha.  Yeah, no doubt.  I was just a kid and kind of indestructible.  We fought a lot."

"That's very unfortunate. I hope my two kids never fight that way. Are you on good terms with your brother now?"
"We are great friends now.  I don't get to see him so much since I'm on tour with my band."

"I'm happy to hear that, I hope you get to seem him soon. Maybe he can come to see one of your shows."
"Yeah, he's been to a few.  I was hoping we could do X-mas with the whole family.  Maybe next year."

"I don't know how Christmas is gonna go with my family this year either... it's hard to be divorced when there's two kids mixed in."
"Divorce is the WORST.  I, too, am divorced.  Worst experience of my life.  I don't speak to my ex."

"I'm sorry to hear that. It's very hard. I'm just ready to be done with the process."
"It will get better over time.  Focus on your kids if you can.  It's gotta be rough.  Oh and get another partner!"

"Oh, that's the same year my son was born.  Do you have kids?"
"Yes I have 3 and big kid (husband)."

"Ha that's funny.  Some men never grow up."
"Yes do your kids still live at home?"

"No my kids are grown and have moved out.  Its kind of quiet sometimes but I like to get out and hike."
"Yes it is nice when they are independent, I didnt think I would adjust as well as I am."

"Do they live close enough to see them when you want?"
"Real close!  With me, LOL ;-) But they are in college and busy with work and school."

"Oh that's an exciting time.  Two of my 3 live nearby but my oldest is 1800 miles away on the west coast"
"My oldest is talking of a move to California, how do feel about the distance with a child?"

"Well it is difficult but you just have to make time to go see them.  He lives in a gorgeous area and I can hike alot there."
"Yes it is nice to have a common interest and that you enjoy vacation there.  Any grandkids yet?"

"yes 4 grandkids and that is very fun.  Be wary of California with all the wildfires"
"I KNOW!  We visited LA last November and brought masks"

"It's unfortunate.  My son is in Oregon and they struggle all summer long"
"Oh gosh, the smoke is there too?  I didnt know that."

A caregiver is someone who takes care of people who cannot ordinarily take care of themselves.
I did a little bit of that when I was in college.  I took care of a few autistic adults.  It was emotional.

That must have been an interesting experience. I've read about adults with autism, it sounds quite difficult. What did you learn from the experience?
One thing was how big their personalities could be.  My guy was hilarious.  He told great jokes!

That's very interesting. What did you go into after college?
I went to work in Silicon Valley for a semiconductor company.  I should have tried out for Dancing with the Stars!

That sounds like a cool job. I dropped out of high school, and a few years later started a small business with my dad.

You can do it! I'm more of an athlete. I have travelled lots for competitions which was great. Have you travelled anywhere?
Last year, I went to Belarus. It was really interesting, the country is almost lost in time. Have you ever been to Eastern Europe?

ughhhh i was proud that i graduated but i don't do anything with my degree
"Well you should be proud of graduating.  Why didn't you do anything with your degree?"

Because whenever I get an interview they always say "we decided to move forward with someone else". It's too much work to keep going to those stupid interviews anyways.
"Well you will never get in if you don't keep trying?  What are you doing instead?"

Just watching Shark Tank. They have it so easy. I just have to think of something that'll sell and then I'll never have to work! 
"Well that seems like a lot of work and a little risky but I am sure you can think of a good idea"

I know right? It's why I can't think of anything. I wish that I was more imaginative and could think of something. What do you watch? 
"well I like Naked and afraid but I would never do the show.  I have problems with interviews too when they see my hair"

OMG that's so much work. And what's wrong with your hair? I bet you have nicer hair than me though 
"Really?  My hair is blue and orange right now"

like Auburn? Do you watch college football? I love Auburn's team 
"I watch some college football but not a lot.  My hair is blue and orange now but will be pink and purple next"

"Not really. Let's talk about food. What do you like to eat? I LOVE fish"
"I like fish too. But really I am not picky. Do you eat a lot of fish?"
"I eat pretty much only fish. My parents do too, and they're both over 6 feet. Probably cause of the fish LOL"
"Possibly. How do you like to prepare your fish?"
"I LOVE salmon. Sear it with some rosemary, lots of butter, and some lemon. to DIE FOR."
"That sounds wonderful - what do you like for side dishes? I eat lots of veggies"
"Some shittake mushrooms and asparagus stirfried with olive oil - I'm a big keto fan so it suits fish"
"I like the way you think - and EAT! Sounds very healthy"
"I'm just worried about where I get my fish - sometime i get scared about mercury and other toxins"
"Yes, I have that worry too - you can never be sure, can you?"
"It's why I pay extra for wild salmon and organic stuff - call me a health nut but when I'm 95 who's laughing? LOL"
"95? That's amazing. Maybe you should write a book"

من تقریباً فقط ماهی می‌خورم. پدر و مادرم هم همینطورن و هر دو بالای ۶ فوت قد دارند. احتمالاً به خاطر ماهیه LOL

من عاشق ماهی سالمون هستم. آن را با کمی رزماری، زیادی کره و کمی لیمو تفت دهید. برای مرگ خوب است.

چند قارچ شیتاکه و اسپراگوس با روغن زیتون تفت داده شده - من طرفدار بزرگ کتو هستم، بنابراین برای ماهی مناسب است.

من فقط نگران این هستم که از کجا ماهی بگیرم - گاهی اوقات از جیوه و سایر سموم میترسم

این دلیلی است که برای ماهی سالمند و مواد آلی اضافی پرداخت می کنم - مرا یک علاقه‌مند به سلامتی بخوانید اما وقتی ۹۵ ساله هستم که چه کسی خندان است؟ LOL

column3:
"I usually watch matches with relatives. It's sort of a family tradition!"
"That's awesome! Family traditions are the best! Did you do anything for Halloween? It was an excuse to eat chocolate for me."

"I bought a lot of candy to hand out, but not many kids showed up! So now I'm stuck with a lot of chocolate, and way too much candy!"
"Hey, that sounds like a win to me! More candy for you! What do you like to do for fun?"

"I play for my college's basketball team. Between that and my studies, I don't have much free time. What about you?"
"That sounds fun! I'm pretty busy with studies too but i like to geocache with my boyfriend. What do you study? "

"That's really cool. I'm studying education, hoping to become a teacher. What are your career ambitions?"
"Cool! My boyfriend is in education as well and is on his first placement. I'm in my senior year of psychiatric nursing. Are you enjoying it?"

"Very interesting. I am enjoying it, yes. I'm a bit nervous about entering the job market though. Congrats to your boyfriend! What got you interested in psychiatric nursing?"
"Well we always need new amazing teachers so I'm sure you'll be fine. I was very interested in both nursing and pscyhology and that's psych nursing!"

"Thank you. It sounds like you've found the perfect career fit!"
"You too! I'm sure you will make a fabulous teacher and I wish you the best!"

Well she was doing quite well with putting books on the shelf at least. So she should be good to go. AT least she isn't like me, 2 years pre med, 2 kids, divorced. I wish I had a job that calming!
Well working as a librarian can be calming for the most part for sure. Sometimes that quiet time gets annoying though. I am not used to the quiet! It must be a lot of organizing for you every day.
I haven't been working here long so it isn't bad so far. I imagine I'll get tired of the sorting eventually though. yes! Yin and yang, balance in all things. You'll do great there.
I love the learning part. Like just the other day I ran across this book "Swimming for Dummies" which was terrific since I don't know how to swim! i think you might be able to teach yourself but its better to get professionally taught.
You might be right about that. Being an adult, I have so much anxiety over water as a result. oh yes anxiety is a terrible thing, you are brave to deal with it. It won't take that long and you'll be squared away
Yep, or at the bottom of a lake somewhere. So how was med school anyway? honestly it was boring! The hours are brutal. It's nice knowing I am able to save lives and help others.

"We have been away past 2 weekends and I just want to be home, plus I'm sick."
"That's okay. You can't be good at everything! Do you have any plans for this weekend?"
"Yes me too, I have been sick with cold going on 4 weeks."
"That's okay. You can't be good at everything! Do you have any plans for this weekend?"
"I was actually the first week and had my flu shot then."
"That's understandable. It's nice to relax at home. I hope you get better soon!"
"I was home sick, but we had trick or treaters!"
"Yikes that's a long time! Have you been to a doctor?"
"Not yet, have you?"
"Oh okay. Hopefully they get the flu shot right this year. I still have to get it. Did you celebrate Halloween yesterday?"
"Not yet, have you?"
"That's good! Hopefully you'll be healthy for Christmas at least! Have you started shopping for that already?"

column3:
"I'm trying to lose weight for my upcoming skiing competition! Do you do any sports? "
"Not, really. I just go to work in bicycle sometimes."

"That's awesome! Great for both you and the environment! Where do you work?"
"I take care of kids at a family house. It is about 20 minutes in bicycle. "

'That sounds like an awesome job! I love kids. Do you have any of your own or want any in the future?'
'I don´t  have any kids yet. But I want to some day. Do you have kids?'

"Yeah I have two kids! A one year old boy and a 3 year old girl. No regrets! What do you like to do for fun?"
"Those are great ages! I love outdoor activities in my big yard. I like BBQ and playing cards or just chilling in summer."

"Oh man that sounds so nice! I'm looking out my window at the snow and missing summer. Do you live somewhere hot or do you get snow too?"
"I get a lot of snow, Which I find interesting too, but also miss summer. Where do you live?"

'I live in Canada. I hate the cold, its unbearable! Where do you live? '
"Ohh. Haven´t you thought about moving? I live in West Virginia, USA."

"I got a job as an account, I've been here for three months now. I'm crushing it :-)"
'Wow Congrats! I recently got a job as a radio host! I love it.'

"Interesting! what time of day do you work? "
"Usually early mornings because that's when people are commuting to work. What about you?"

"that's the only time of day I listen to the radio! My hours are regular office hours. I am really enjoying my new gig. sounds like you are too? "
'Ahh so the typical 9-5? My husband is the same, but he usually works overtime by having to go to corporate dinners haha. Yeah I love it.'

'Yep exactly. Do you get lots of people calling in to your show? '
'Not usually, people only really call in for the competitions we run. '

"ah ha. I've actually called in and won on radio shows before! do you get decent vacation time? "
"Really?! What did you win? Yeah, it's the standard amount you'd expect really, but every day feels like a holiday when you love your job :)"

"I totally agree! You gotta do what you love, find the right mix of people! I've won concert tickets!"
'Wow really? To see who? I recently went to see BTS live, that was absolutely amazing. I love any type of pop music haha.'

"Well, those are all numbers."
"that's true. in theory the numbers work, but you can only know for sure once the solar panels are installed."
"I'd love to have the panels but math isn't my strong point."
'maybe a qualified electrician in the field can help you crunch the numbers.'
"that would be most good."
"now, i need your advice. my mom is allergic to dogs and i've got two dogs as pets. how can i make my home inviting for mom?"
"Can the dogs be put in another room when she visits?"
'i do that already, though she still gets symptoms. maybe i can use solar power to power a uv allergen zapper.'
"Now that's a new idea! I love it."
'since we both would like to install panels, I think we should arrange for the same company to do the work.'
"Do you know anyone who's had it done? Someone who could offer recommendation?"
"Yes, my brother had his whole house off grid with Green Solars Energy. Great company and affordable."

yes. I am excited about it. What is the longest you have been in one?

"I listen to blues, mostly. I've been collecting blues years." 
"That's cool! Do you have any band reccomendations? I'm always looking for things to add to my spotify playlist."

"I definitely recommend checking out the work of B.B. King. Ever listened to him?" 
"Nope. I've honestly never heard of him. I'm looking him up right now. What else do you like to do for fun?"

"I like playing instruments. My friends and I recently started a garage band, that's been a lot of fun. What about you?" 
"That's so cool! What kind of music do you play? I like hanging out with my dog and playing video games."

"Nice, what kinds of video games? I like video games too. My band and I mostly play classic rock. I'm on the bass guitar." 
"All of them! Right now I'm playing through Borderlands 3. It's a lot of fun! That's super cool. Do you perform ever or just play for fun?"

"Borderlands 3, very cool.I was thinking of trying it. What character are you playing? And yeah, we mostly play weddings, honestly!" 
"I'm playing as FL4K! It's really buggy right now but its still awesome. That's super cool. Maybe I'll hire you to play mine one day!"

"Nice, I was of playing FL4K too. I'm mostly absorbed by the new Modern Warfare lately though, haha. And that would be cool! Do you have a partner?" 
"What system do you play on? Yeah I have a boyfriend of almost 3 years. Do you have a partner? What country are you in?"

"I play on ps4. And cool! I got out a relationship about a month ago. I'm from Canada. And you?" 
"Oh no sorry to hear that! We have a ps4, xbox one, and switch between the two of us! I'm also in Canada - Manitoba."

Is your grandmother OK?
My grandmother is. She passed away 5 years ago. Now my mom is sick.

so sorry, I thought you said grandmother -- not focused lately.  I am retiring in 6 months
I know. Sadly she passed away from Alzheimer's. I hope my mom is not getting the same. She is much better now. But I have a lot to pay.

yes, it can be very expensive.  I hope you all have good insurance
We do, but still a lot of bills. It is ok, health is important. That's why you need to be active! I used to run fast but I stopped.

Agreed, I have studied ballet all my life to stay activbe
That is great. I like to watch ballet. It requires a lot of discipline, right?

It sure does.  Alot of discipline and alot of practicve
I bet! If I ever have a girl I would love for her to practice ballet.

It is really great, almost meditative.  You have no children?
No. I don't. But I would like to. Maybe in one or two years. What about you?

"My job is a total deadend. Selling things no one wants. Literally the only good thing is that it's 9-5 w/no overtime"
"I enjoy working with the public,do you?"

"I do, but I don't like feeling like I'm trying to scam people when selling them stuff...so I need to look for a new gig"
"Well as a bank teller you don't scam people"

"right - maybe I should try that! do you need to have experience? "
"Most teller jobs need experience with handling cash and a high school diploma. so you would have to have some expirience in the field"

"ok I've done multiple retail jobs and I am def a hs graduate, plus I'm sick of sales. I'll look for openings"
"well now most provide on-the-job training.so you will get all the training you need there"

"sounds perfect! my other alternative would be working at Costco...after all, it's my favorite place to shop!"
"I love going to Costco."

"Me too! I need to head over there and check out some of their stuff for Christmas!"
"You should - it has something for everyone."

'I know! or basketball...or maybe some other kind of team!'
'Yup, I guess it depends on what sports your kids like. '

"or maybe they won't like sports at all...you never know! We might end up with an artist!"
"You never know! Hopefully they don't turn out like me... I'm a recovering alcoholic and I was living in a storage locker for two months."

"that sounds rough. Are things looking up for you now? Are you going to AA?"
"Yes, I'm attending AA every Sunday. Luckily I'm in an apartment now too, things are finally starting to go my way."

"That's great...I was going to ask about your living situation. It must feel good to be in your own place. "
"Yes, it's so nice to be able to have somewhere to come relax."

"oh, I bet! and I'm guessing the heating/ac was not great in the storage locker? How is your job going? "
"It was always freezing! It's going good, I'm working the night shift at a gas station right now. What about you?"

"actually I have to be on bed rest right now, for my health and the babies. So I'm not working right now. "
"Ah, I hope you enjoy your time not working. How long will you be on bed rest for?"

"I honestly love security, I'm a really big guy, 250lbs and really muscular, maybe I'll become a bouncer."
"That is true! I think you're in the right here, clearly. What sort of job would you like to do if this does not work out?"

"but what if there is a security issue and I'm off helping someone find a product? that could be a really bad situation."
"Do they not have enough security staff available so that you can help customers?"

"probably just spend more time with my dogs. what do you do?"
"I am currently a student, but I am working towards my dream of becoming a fashion designer."

"It's not my job to help customers. I am the only security person."
'Would you have a day job as well if you became a bouncer or security guard that works at night?'

"oh that sounds exciting! "
"Yeah! I would like to create a more affordable stylish brand that looks similar to LV or Gucci."

"I like that idea. Even though i'ma big guy i really like fashion"
"I was going to say something earlier but maybe you could be a model for my future stuff! You did say you're big and muscular."

column3:
I think daycares are underrated. They let kids have so much expression and creativity and the employees should be paid more for that.
Yes I agree most daycare workers are underpaid it's a very difficult job 

Agreed! Kids require patience that it seems like many of us don't have.
another thing I think that can be under estmiated is the fact that a lot of kids come from broken homes and have emotional trouble

Exactly! Its heart breaking, and i hope daycares are well aware of that when some kids act a certain way.
maybe it would help if they had some type of music program, I always found music relaxing and love all types, do You like music?

Interesting suggestion! I absolutely LOVE music. What genre would you suggest would help?
I think every genere can help in some way I would love to teach both a mix of clasical and indie mixed togeter like radiohead mixed with mozart

Fair point. I personally haven't indulged in indie music but now you've got me interested!
Lol that's cool radiohead is one of my fav, what are some of your fav bands.

I like this R&B and soul band called the internet. I have a thing for the R&B era! How about you?
I like the old shool R&B like Aaliyah, Timberland, Usher, and such It's been great talking to You

من فکر می‌کنم مراقبت از کودکان کمتر ارزش‌گذاری شده است. آنها به کودکان اجازه می‌دهند که بیشتر بیان و خلاقیت داشته باشند و کارکنان باید بزرگترین حقوق را برای این کار دریافت کنند.

موافقم! بچه‌ها نیاز به صبر دارند که به نظر می‌رسد بسیاری از ما نداریم.

دقیقا! این واقعاً دلخراش است، و من امیدوارم مهد کودک ها این موضوع را در نظر بگیرند وقتی برخی از کودکان به یک شیوه خاص عمل می کنند.

پیشنهاد جالبیه! من عاشق موسیقی هستم. ژانری که پیشنهاد می‌کنید چیه که کمک کنه؟

نقطه قوی. من شخصاً به موسیقی مستقل علاقه‌ای نداشتم اما اکنون شما من را علاقه‌مند کرده‌اید!

من این گروه R&B و soul به نام اینترنت را دوست دارم. من علاقه‌ای به دوره R&B دارم! شما چطور؟
column5:
بله، موافقم که بیشتر کارگران مراقبت از کودکان پول کمی دریافت می‌کنند، این یک شغل بسیار دشوار است.

یک چیز دیگری که فکر می‌کنم ممکن است کمتر ارزش‌گذاری شود این است که بسیاری از کودکان از خانواده‌های شکسته آمده و مشکلات عاطفی دارند.

شاید کمک کند اگر آن‌ها یک برنامه موسیقی داشتند، من همیشه موسیقی را آرام‌بخش می‌یابم و از همه انواع آن لذت می‌برم، آیا شما هم موسیقی را دوست دارید؟

فکر می‌کنم هر سبک موسیقی به نحوی می‌تواند کمک کند. دوست دارم هر دوی یک ترکیب از کلاسیک و ایندی را به هم مخلوط کنم، مانند رادیوهد با موزارت.

ههه، این خیلی باحاله، ردیوهد یکی از مورد علاقه‌های منه، باندهای مورد علاقه‌ات چیا هستن؟

من موسیقی R&B قدیمی مانند آلیا، تیمبرلند، آشر و موارد مشابه را دوست دارم. خوشحالم که با شما صحبت کردم.

Pushing yourself to do better is always a good idea! Sometimes I honestly feel like I push myself too often.
It can be really hard. Nobody should push themselves too hard. It can be stressful.

Well when someone focuses on perfectionism they don't really take into account its affects.
I agree. Also very hard on the perfectionist person. Hard for them to accept if they don't make their goals.

Very true, they treat it like it's the end of the world.
I agree.  Do you set any goals for yourself?

Yes absolutely. Sometimes I believe my goals are too strict or hard to reach.
What kind of goals do you set? Like for work or what?

I set goals around my work and school. With school I force myself to shoot for the stars and I have to follow every regulation at work.
My daughter just graduated top of her class. She knows what that is like. She is a perfectionist too

Are you calling me a perfectionist? How could you tell?
No my daughter. She just graduated high school with honors

خب وقتی کسی بر روی کمال‌گرایی تمرکز می‌کند، واقعاً تأثیرات آن را در نظر نمی‌گیرد.

بسیار درست است، آن را مثل انتهای دنیا می‌پندارند.

من اهدافی را درباره کار و مدرسه‌ام تعیین می‌کنم. در مدرسه، خودم را مجبور می‌کنم تا به ستارگان برسم و در کار باید هر دستورالعملی را رعایت کنم.

column3:
"I do, but not much anymore. Do you?"
"I used to have a dirt bike, but don't anymore either. Some of my family ride in groups and events."
"Why did you stop cycling?"
"Mountain biking accident. Couldn't afford to replace my bike afterwards."
"Oh no! That's awful. Did you get hurt in the accident?"
" Only my pride was hurt. I have a friend who does some tests to show riding skills and I tried to copy her. It didn't work out so well."
"Oof! What a bummer. Hopefully your pride has recovered since then. :)"
"Mostly recovered. I don't think I'll be trying to show off like that again, though!"
"I don't blame you one bit. Do you have any other hobbies to take its place?"
"I take time on the weekends to hike up in Canada. The views up there are great."
"Oh wow. I've never been, but I'd like to go one day. Friends who have traveled there absolutely love it."
"Yeah you should go! Or to any lake/camping area near where you live. You would have a great time too!"

column3:
I wish I could draw tattoos!
It's definitely an art to get good at tattooing, you can't exactly go back and erase a mistake when it's permanent!
I know and that's why you need to find a really good artist to get your tattoo done
What would you say is your best way of finding a really good tattoo artist? I am a designer myself but I don't know anyone who tattoos professionally.
I have an artist who's been doing tattoos for me for years now
Cool! I really love how tattooing is becoming more acceptable recently, although I'm not brave enough to get one myself. Does it hurt getting one?
Yes, little bit but it's worth it!
Have you ever tried designing one yourself? I have been considering it as there seems to be quite a lot of demand for original tattoo designs.
You're right! I never tried myself but I thing you should definitelly go for it!
I'd love to but I'd be too worried that someone wouldn't like my design. Can you imagine if someone said they didn't like it after the tattoo was already finished?
that would be hard!
Luckily I think tattoo removals have become pretty advanced these days, a bad drawing has to be better than getting another persons name tattooed on you though!

من می دانم و به همین دلیل باید یک هنرمند واقعا خوب پیدا کنید تا تاتوی خود را انجام دهید.

من یک هنرمند دارم که سال‌هاست برای من تاتو انجام می‌دهد.

بله، کمی اما ارزش دارد!

شما درست می‌گویید! من هرگز خودم امتحان نکردم اما فکر می‌کنم حتما باید اقدام کنید!

این کار سخت خواهد بود!

خوبه، خیلی خوبه. من عاشق سگ ها هستم و می‌خواهم یک دوبرمن دیگر بگیرم.

من فقط دارم استراحت می‌کنم و زودی شام می‌پزم، چند تکه گوشت خوک داری؟ تو خوردی؟

بله، فکر می‌کنم آخر هفته به ساحل بروم، بنابراین باید آرامش بخش باشد. امیدوارم که دوست داشته باشم. من عاشق سفر کردن هستم، آیا برنامه‌ای برای این آخر هفته دارید؟

صدای خوبی می‌دهد. آیا هر بجنبان تلویزیونی آینده‌ای که دوست دارید دارید؟

آینه سیاه برنامه مورد علاقه من در نتفلیکس است. من اصلاً عاشق آن هستم. قسمت مورد علاقه من پانزده میلیون مرتبه است. آیا آن را دیده‌ای؟

این عالی است و یک چیز خوب این است که می‌توانید آن‌ها را به هر ترتیبی تماشا کنید زیرا همه آن‌ها متفاوت هستند.

نه، من ندارم، من گرسنه ام هاها گوشت چرخ کرده خوشمزه به نظر می رسد

احتمالاً این هفته‌اند خونه می‌مونم و آروم می‌گیرم. من و کالیمون می‌ریم تعدادی بیسکویت سگی بخریم.

بله، من سریال "چیزهای عجیب" را دوست دارم، واقعاً خیلی دوست دارم سریال "آینه سیاه" را ببینم. آیا شما دیده‌اید؟

نه اما من می‌میرم که آن را بررسی کنم.

عالیه. خیلی دوست دارم ببینم. یک کلیپ دیدم که مردم امتیازات اجتماعی داشتند.

"Well, my mother might be some that believes that... she has 500 pairs of shoes for crying out loud!"
"Oh wow. What does she say she wants with all those shoes?"

"She just tells me that she can't give them up because he thinks that something awful will happen to me if she does."
"Are they her shoes, or did they used to be yours? That seems a little odd!"

"They're shoes that she sees and buys. There are some that used to be mine or my fathers but most are just shoes that she sees at stores."
"Huh, interesting. But she thinks something bad will happen to you if she gives up the shoes? Bad like what?"

"I'm allergic to a lot of different things like shellfish, cats, etc. So something like I'll get scratched by a cat and die. Who knows!"
"Well, I guess moms will mom as they want! Hahaha. Is her house really cluttered with all those shoes?"

"No, I have "left the nest" as they say. My father and mother both live in the town I grew up in."
"Good for you. :) Life happened to me in a pretty rough way, so I'm currently in my folks' basement...but it's a place!"

"Hey at least you have your family close by! What happened if you don't mind me asking?"
"My roommate committed suicide two years ago, and I couldn't make the bills without her. But my parents let me save money, so I'm glad for them."

"Yeah, it's a really good idea with all the floods happening on the coast. And likewise! Do you have to go?"
"No I dont have to go now, it was nice talking to you when I saw you at the grocery store"

"Oh, yes! I remember now. It was great to catch up. :) How'd your dinner go?"
"It went great, that new restaurant in town is fantastic but I had to take a walk after such a good meal"

"I wish I could walk after a good meal. Normally I have to nap instead!"
"Haha, sounds like you're my new cat, she always naps after she eats"

"I love cats! I have five of them. Is she your only one?"
"Yeah, we're only allowed one pet at the apartment we're at. Eventually we'd get another"

"We started off with two because I convinced my husband that kittens go better in pairs. :) The rest are coincidental! How old is your kitty?"
"Shes just a couple months! We got her as a rescue, someone had abandoned her"

"Oh nooo poor baby! Good on you for taking her in! They're so much fun (but also big buttheads) at that age. What color is she?"
"She's a calico, she is too cute, I need to show you some pictures!"

'Writing stuff down is a great way to remember what you want to say. How was your day other than that?'

"My day was pretty good. After the speech there wasn't much to do at work. How about your day?"
"It was okay. Just boring. Can't wait to get home and read. What do you like to do in your free time?"

"I try to stay busy with various hobbies like sports and outdoor activities. I also like reading as well. Any good books you've read lately?"
"Well my favorite is horror novels. My favorite author is Stephen King. What kind of books do you like?"

"I like mostly history. However, I do really like Stephen King. Have you read Christine?"
"No but I have heard of it. It's on my list. My favorite Stephen King book is Misery"

"Misery is a good one too. I also liked the movie adaptation with James Cann."
"I do too. Kathy Bates did a great job in that film."

"Yeah, she was cast perfectly for that role. I wonder if that movie is on Netflix or Hulu, I haven't seen it in a while."
"Me either. What is your favorite genre of movies?"

Have you ever played chess before?
"I don't play myself, but my son is good and is teaching my grandson. He's probably better than me lol"

That's so cool! My father taught me chess. He learned to play when he was a boy in Greece.
"It's so nice when families keep things like that going. Do you have any other hobbies?"

Oh yes, I draw. I've been doing that since I moved to the US.
"I draw also! And I bake. Don't have much of a sweet tooth so most of it goes to my kids, but I like doing it"

Oh awesome! do any of your kids have the same passion for drawing?
"One does. Do you have any kids?"

None that I know of. Haha! I wish I could get into baking but I'm afraid I'm too old to learn at this point in my life.
"Oh no, baking is easy. If you can follow directions, you can bake lol"

That's what everyone says, but I've tried and it always comes out burnt or severely underdone.
"Well I suppose there is a learning curve. Bread is probably best to start with"

"Thats awesome! Do you like browsing social media?"

"I agree. What would you say is your favorite platform?"

column3:
"I didn't realize dentistry went back that far?"
Yup! In fact I have heard archaeologists have discovered mummified ancients with metal bands wrapped around individual teeth

"I wonder how they were able to do that fine of metalwork thousands of years ago?"
Beats me... the only reason I know this is because I've been doing a lot of research in hopes I can convince my mom that I shouldn't get braces.

"LOL! I didn't get braces when I was a kid, but I should have. You may not like them now, but it will definitely be worth it years later."
Yes, but I suppose it's worth it in the long run.  But I hate the idea of having metal in my mouth.

"There are new braces that are clear plastic that you wear at night, they make new ones as your teeth get realigned"
I wonder if those would also help stop food getting between your teeth.

"They might as they cover the teeth, but you mostly wear them while you are sleeping."
I didn't know if you wore them during the day while you. I tend to be eating all the time. I probably need to stop eating so much.

"Friends that had regular braces did have to watch a lot of what they ate and had to cut some things out."
I don't think my mom would let me get the clear braces you're talking about. Probably just to embarrass me.

من نفهم نکردم که دندانپزشکی تا این حد قدیمی است؟

من تعجب می‌کنم که آنها چگونه قدرت کردند این نوع کارهای فلزی را هزاران سال پیش انجام دهند؟

ههه! وقتی کودک بودم از این دندان‌های زیبا استفاده نکردم، اما باید می‌کردم. شاید الان دوست نداشته باشی، اما قطعا سال‌ها بعد ارزشش را خواهد داشت.

دستگاه‌های ارتودنسی جدیدی وجود دارند که از پلاستیک شفاف ساخته شده‌اند و شما آن‌ها را شب‌ها می‌پوشیدید. آن‌ها هر زمان که دندان‌های شما بازمی‌گردند، دستگاه‌های جدیدی برای شما ساخته می‌شوند.

آنها ممکن است زمانی که دندان ها را پوشش دهند، اما شما بیشتر آنها را زمانی که خوابیده اید می پوشید.

دوستانی که از بریس های معمولی استفاده می کردند، باید بسیاری از غذاها را مصرف نکردند و برخی از چیزها را حذف می کردند.
column5:
بله! در واقع من شنیده‌ام که باستان‌شناسان مومیایی‌های باستانی را کشف کرده‌اند که دندان‌های فردی را با باندهای فلزی پیچیده‌اند

من نمی‌دونم... تنها دلیلی که این رو می‌دونم اینه که خیلی تحقیق کردم امیدوارم بتونم مامانم رو متقاعد کنم که نباید دندان‌هایم را برقرار کنم.

بله، اما فکر می‌کنم در نهایت ارزش دارد. اما من از این فکر کردن که فلز در دهانم دارم متنفرم.

من تعجب می‌کنم که آیا این‌ها هم می‌توانند کمک کنند تا غذا بین دندان‌های شما گیر نکند.

من نمی‌دانستم که آیا شما آن‌ها را در طول روز می‌پوشیدید یا نه. من به تمام وقت غذا می‌خورم. احتمالا باید کمتر غذا بخورم.

فکر نمی‌کنم مادرم اجازه بدهد که اون بریس های شفافی که در موردش صحبت می‌کنی را بگیرم. احتمالا فقط برای شرمندگی من.

شما هم. من واقعاً از برنامه‌های قدیمی خوشم می‌آید و به تازگی تمام چهار فصل مسیر 66 را تماشا کردم، قطعاً یک برنامه بسیار خوب از اوایل دهه 60 بود.

'yeah exactly, and it's good to use up vegetables that are about to go bad too.'

"That would be true if I ate vegetables haha. I really need to start eating healthier.  "

"I think it's more economic too"
"Yes and no. While many people save money from not buying meat, supplementing the vitamins and protein meat gives you can be expensive."

"I don't think you need to take supplements as a vegetarian. Have you ever tried skipping meat?"
"There are some things you can't get from vegetables alone. I might consider going vegetarian, it's just skipping meat."

"It might not be easy at first but there are many interesting veggie options out there."
"What interests me is veggie versions of meat products. I really want to try the impossible whopper."

"I've never tried that one but it sounds yummy"
"I've heard good things about it. I love the taste of meat so I am really interested in things like that, would make going vegetarian easier."

"For sure. Going vegetarian is so much easier than vegan. I couldn't leave without cheese!"
"I agree, I would give up if I couldn't have any cheese."

"Me too! And what do you think about gluten-free diet?"
"Well, I don't think it's necessary if you don't have a gluten allergy or celiac's disease. I've heard it can lower blood sugar for diabetics though."

When not studying, I train for marathons. Running really clears my head. What branch of law do you want to work in?
Criminal law. What about you?
Criminal Law also. I believe there are too many people incarcerated unjustly due to our societal injustices. Will you defend or prosecute?
I agree with you. I would like to go into defence, do you have a preference?
I guess I could go either way and support my cause but most likely I will be a defense attorney. I don't have any political goals. You?
I don't, but I follow politics very closely. I find having an understanding of the political climate helps with my studies. Would you agree?
Absolutely. Politics and law go hand in hand. I love a good debate. Do you have lawyers in your family?

'I think you might be right, the Mr.Pickles might truly be a possessed demon cat haha'

'Do you have any other animals?'

column3:
"I had it for 4 years. I was given it by my older sister for my birthday. It's a sad day... Do you have any pets?"
"Yeah I have one dog called cody."
"Aw, that's cute name for a dog. And how long have you had him?"
"for three years this winter. We got him for the kids but it turns out I needed him more than them when they left for university haha."
"Kids move on very quickly when they go to university, but it's great that Cody can keep you company! After 3 years, he must be like family now"
"He definitly is! He's my baby now, along with the children I teach at school :) What od"
"You're a teacher? And what do you teach? :) I don't know if I would be able to become a teacher haha"
"I teach year two students, so it's not that difficult because they're just learning to count haha. You could! It's not difficult, you just need patience :)"
"Ahh, year two students definitely don't sound as bad as year 9 haha! But that's the thing, patience is necessary, and it's exhausting!"
"It is exhausting! But at least I get a lot of holiday time to recover haha! Do you have a job?"
"And are summer and winter holidays paid at all? Cause that's how long all together 4-5months?  But no, I'm currently at university :)"
"Ohhh that's interesting, what do you study? I loved university so much. Yes there's good holiday pay thankfully :)"
"I study politics and international relations, definitely an exciting degree in today's world haha :)"
"Wow for sure! I'm in England so Brexit has been all over the news every day haha. Anyway I wish you luck with it!! :)"

column3:
"Sometimes the best part of Halloween is staying in and watching some horror flicks, that's what I like to do!"
"Horror flicks? Don't you ever get too scared? Haha! I'm not a fan of horrors, much prefer old British comedy tv shows"
"I do, but that's the fun of it! Have you ever seen Only Fools and Horses?"
"But when the movies finish, are you not scared that some of the horror things may happen to you?? Haha! But yes, I love only fools and horses!"
"Nope, I've made it so far in one piece! Who is your favorite character?"
"I watched a bit of paranormal activity and I just got too scared, it was too real haha! Rodney was my favourite. Who's your favourite?"
"Del Boy! Such a good show, I love the theme music. Do you like music?"
"Yes, I love music! I used to play guitar and piano when I was younger (used to be pretty good haha). Do you like music?"
"Yeah, I play guitar mainly. I want to be a music teacher! What's your favorite piece to play?"
"Why a music teacher and not a performer? But my favourite piece, hm, I played flamenco guitar - so 'asturias', such a good piece"
"I do perform, mostly on weekends, but I really enjoy working with new people who are keen to learn! Figured I could make a more reliable career out of it."
"It must take a lot of patience to be able to teach new people to play! I tried to teach my grandson, but he just didn't want to listen haha"

column3:
"Mice aren't as bad as everyone thinks they are."
"I've got a fear of rodents, I don't like them in general. But why do you think that mice aren't as bad?"

"They help keep other pests like insects away"
"Okay, I agree here. To keep the biodiversity, mice are necessary. But keeping them as pets isn't the necessary"

"That's true its not, mine are kids to me. We watch Dr.Who together."
"You watch Dr.Who with mice? Haha, interesting. And have you read Dr.Who books?"

"I can't have books, the mice eat the pages."
"That's a shame. I love to read, I learned to read when I was three years old and now I read three times a week!"

"Reading is a fun way to take an adventure, before I got my mice I would read. What are your favorite types of books?"
"I love reading academic books and books about history! Books about Chinese, Russian and French history are fascinating!"

"Do you know how to speak those languages?"
"Sadly, I can only read about Chinese history in English, but I can speak the other languages. They are so fun!"

"Bacon should be, and if you think about it, it's meat candy. It's so versatile as well."
"I've never thought of it like that but it is. My favorite is using bacon with veggies, makes them taste better."
"Agreed, bacon with green beans is a great side dish."
"I like to wrap it around asparagus topped with cheese."
"Now that sounds really good! I may have to try that some time. Have you ever used bacon mixed with ground beef for a burger?"
"Yes I have I add peppers into the mix as well to give it a kick."
"Good trick, what type of bacon do you normally use? I prefer peppered bacon or thick cut."
"I like applewood smoked."
"That's a good type too, perfect on a BLT"
"Yes it is, or I crumbled it and make bacon cheeseburger eggrolls. Which is so delicious."
"that sounds pretty good, I'll have to try that later!"
"I think Bacon should be it's own food group."

صاحبخانه اجازه نگهداری حیوانات خانگی را نمی‌دهد تا کف‌ها را نابود نکنند.

بله، بیشتر اوقات خوبه اما ممکنه آزاردهنده باشه. ما به هم شبیهیم، پس اذیت کننده است که مردم همیشه ما را اشتباه بگیرند.

بله، من هم یک نفر کوتاه واقعی هستم، پس من همیشه این را می‌فهمم. علاوه بر این، به عنوان یک مرد، مردم فکر می‌کنند عجیب است که سرگرمی مورد علاقه من پخت کیک است.

من حدود 20 سال است که کیک می‌پزم، از هفت سالگی شروع کردم. واقعاً وقتی 14 سال داشتم به فرآیند تزئین علاقه‌مند شدم.

استعداد بخشی از آن است اما من برای کسب هر چه بیشتر دانش و تکنیک ممکن، زیاد مطالعه کرده‌ام. من به دنبال اطلاعات جدید به طور مداوم هستم.

column3:
"It's so hot there! I don't know how anyone could live there in the summer."
"Agreed! Hot and humid... and rainy! I like to see the seasons, especially winter! My favorite!"

"I wen't to Disney World with my kids during vacation once. It rained for almost 5 days!"
"Oh no!! That is bad! I hope that did not ruin your vacation."

"I had to wait in line for hours in the rain. It has horrible."
"I hope the kids did not get a cold!"

"They didn't, thank god. Could have been way worse I guess."
"Yeah! I usually take vitamin c all the time just to prevent colds. You should do the same with the kids! Thank god no cold after all that rain."

"Thanks for the tip! Does vitamin C really prevent colds?"
"Yeah! and Zinc! It helps prevent them but it does not make much of a difference once you have it."

"Do you think they will ever find a cure for the cold? It's so annoying."
"It mutates a lot! I hope that they will at some point. We have to be careful with all these mutations though."

من دو فرزند دارم

مطمئن نیستم، با هزینه‌های مراقبت از کودک در این روزها اتفاقاً تصمیم تجاری هم می‌شود.

این درست است - این بانواقع شبیه حیوانات خانگی است. و قدرت تشکیل ذهن و زندگی آنها مسئولیت بزرگی است.

من یک سگ و یک گربه دارم - بچه های من همیشه دوست دارند با آنها بازی کنند و در حالی که آنها این کار را می کنند، به من فرصتی برای استراحت و خواندن می دهد.

آن‌ها این کار را می‌کنند. گربه‌ی من مانند سگ رفتار می‌کند. و بچه‌هایم آن‌ها را در حیاط دنبال می‌کنند تا انرژی خود را سوزانند.

column3:
"Yeah, I haven't lost a parent yet, so I don't know what to do or say to her."
"Well, I have lost a grandparent as well, and most of the time you don't need to say anything - just be there."

"That's what I've been doing, her family is all coming in, so I've been cleaning and getting food and stuff in"
"That's a good way to be supportive - anything to help her - especially to allow her more time with her family.  Does she like to draw?"

"Yeah, she does. But I'm a truck driver so I have to leave for a few days too. So hopefully her family will be here to help."
"I would make sure that she has family for support and isn't alone.  Drawing is a good coping outlet for me - I draw my feelings and it helps"

"Do you suggest I get her a journal and pencils?"
"A drawing journal would be good so she could draw and write out her feelings.  Gives her a healthy way to release them"

"Yeah! I think thats great! Even one of those that have prompts for her to write or draw."
"Yeah that's true, what does she usually like to draw?  You might encourage her to draw something she likes also to make her happy."

"She likes to draw animals."
"I always liked drawing animals too - I used to go to the zoo and sit and draw the animals."

It is, and working for peta makes life even more difficult PETA?  Wow, I bet.  What do you do there?  Kids would be hard enough without work.
I tend to the animals, being a vegetarian made me appreciate the animals more.  I see.  Noble profession.  I was a vegan for several years.  I have reintroduced fish now.
Fish used to be a favorite of mine, maybe someday I will taste the fine trout again !  Yeah, I only eat fresh caught, non-farm raised.  The Real Deal.  Salmon is my preference.
Ah, Salmon is delicious. Going vegetarian changed all that for me though, now it's plant based only.  I get it.  I usually do fish tacos - one of my favorites.  It's also easy and quick to make at college.
Those are also quite tasty! I miss the days like that.  Yeah, you can still eat the guacamole though!  I'm studying to be a doctor.  So, I wanted to be healthy
That was a great career choice! And yes guacamole fits right into my vegetarianism. Working for peta makes less time for eating though,  Yeah, I'm sure.  But a working for a good cause is meaningful and rewarding - I couldn't imagine having a boring, meaningless job.

ماهی یکی از مورد علاقه‌های من بود، شاید روزی دوباره بتوانم ماهی قزل‌آلا را بچشم! آره، من فقط ماهی‌های تازه گرفته شده و غیر از مزرعه را می‌خورم. ماهی‌های واقعی. ماهی سالمون انتخاب من است.

اینها هم خیلی خوشمزه هستند! از روزهایی مثل اون دلم برایشون تنگ شده. آره، می‌تونی هنوزم گواکاموله بخوری! من دارم برای تبدیل شدن به یک دکتر مطالعه می‌کنم. پس، می‌خواستم سالم باشم.
column5:
من به حیوانات مراقبت می‌کنم، بودن گیاه‌خوار باعث شد حیوانات را بیشتر ارزش بیابم. متوجه شدم. حرفه‌ای شریف. من چند سال گذشته گیاه‌خوار بودم. اکنون مجدداً ماهی را به رژیم غذایی‌ام اضافه کرده‌ام.

آه، ماهی سالمون خیلی خوشمزه است. اما وقتی تصمیم گرفتم گیاه‌خوار شوم، همه چیز تغییر کرد و حالا فقط مبتنی بر گیاه‌ها هستم. من می‌فهمم. من معمولاً تاکو ماهی می‌خورم - یکی از مورد علاقه‌های من. همچنین آن را در دانشگاه آسان و سریع تهیه می‌کنم.

این یک انتخاب شغلی عالی بود! و بله، گواکاموله به خوبی با گیاه‌خواری من هماهنگ است. کار کردن برای پیتا کمتر زمانی برای خوردن می‌گذارد، آره، مطمئنم. اما کار کردن برای یک هدف خوب معنی‌دار و پاداش‌بخش است - نمی‌توانم تصور کنم که یک شغل خسته‌کننده و بی‌معنی داشته باشم.

column3:
"I agree. I enjoy reading books, but I can't find a good blog for books."
"I try not to rely on blogs for information."

"Very true. But blogs can be a great place to voice opinions about things that you read."
"Indeed."

"Do you like to read? Fiction? Nonfiction?"
"I love fantasy and sci-fi. My friends say my library is arranged well, but I still think it could use some improvement."

"I like fantasy and sci-fi as well. I really enjoyed reading the Game of Thrones series. "
"I've never watched it, but I hear that Game of Thrones is a great show."

"It was a great show, wasn't too happy with the ending, so I'm holding out hope for the books. There are still 2 books that he hasn't released yet. "
"I did not know it was ending, sorry to hear that!"

"It's OK. All good things must come to an end right? What about you? Favorite book or series? "
"Wheel of Time is the top one for me, But I also like most of the Brandon Sanderson Novels I've read too. Particularly the Cosmere stuff."

"Not well, I'm a yoga instructor and tried showing him some techniques to help him relax through grieving. Great idea, that is good for the body and mind.  Being there for him alone will help - shows you care."
"You have to be there for your friends. Watch a good romantic comedy with them. Get a nice laugh going. True enough.  "Laughter is the best medicine."  I usually watch movies alone though."
"Not myself. The idea of a romantic comedy alone is boring to me. But being alone can be good for the soul. Yeah, I work in a factory so I don't get a chance to talk to many people.  I like being alone."
"Maybe you should take on Yoga. Great activity for when you're alone! I do like exercise - I've never tried Yoga.  Do you have any suggestions on where to start?"
"Purchase a book at any book shop. It will show you the basics. Then seek out a professional later for more advanced learning! Ok - thanks for the tip.  I'll definitely have to check that out.  I want to stay healthy.  I hope it helps out your friend"
"I do as well.  Keep his minds off things. Then take him to see a wonderful romantic comedy! Yeah, what's your favorite romantic comedy?  You seem to really enjoy them"
"My favorite is Something's gotta give with Jack Nicholson. Wonderful Film! I'll have to check it out - thanks!"

خوب نیست، من مربی یوگا هستم و سعی کردم به او چند تکنیک نشان دهم تا به او کمک کنم که از طریق غمگین شدن آرامش بیابد. ایده عالی است، که برای بدن و ذهن خوب است. حضور در کنار او تنها کمک خواهد کرد - نشان می دهد که شما مراقب او هستید.

نه خودم. ایده یک کمدی عاشقانه تنها برای من خسته کننده است. اما تنها بودن می‌تواند خوب برای روح باشد. آره، من در یک کارخانه کار می‌کنم، بنابراین فرصت صحبت کردن با افراد زیادی ندارم. من دوست دارم تنها باشم.

یک کتاب از هر کتابفروشی بخرید. این به شما مبانی را نشان خواهد داد. سپس برای یادگیری پیشرفته‌تر، به دنبال یک حرفه‌ای بگردید! خب - ممنون بابت نکته. حتما بیاید آن را چک کنم. من می‌خواهم سالم بمانم. امیدوارم به دوست شما کمک کند.

عزیزترین فیلم من "باید چیزی اتفاق بیفته" با بازی جک نیکلسون است. فیلم فوق‌العاده‌ای است! حتما بیاید ببینمش - ممنون!

"Yes! That is actually my favorite type of music."

'Awesome.  Do you like going to see concerts live?  They can get pretty intense.'
'They can. I think its the best part though! You can really feel the music in your bones.'

'Yeah, agreed - I always feed off the energy from the crowd as well - it becomes a full body experience.'
'Truly! I prefer a smaller venue setting as opposed to Music Festivals though, how about you?'

column3:
Yes, and by rooting yourself in the Bible, You can have a strong family bond! 
Yeah, my mom created a strong foundation in the church for me.  We went to Sunday School and the weekly service.

Being a married man, heaped in religion. The Bible is my favorite book. Which book in the bible is yours ? 
I'm not sure I understand your question - but my favorite book in the Bible is Psalms

Yes the Psalms are beautiful. Myself and my wife like reading Psalms before bed for peace of mind. 
I agree - they've always brought me comfort.  Reading in general before bed does for me.  I recently strayed away some though from the Lord

We all stray, but by going back to the good book we can find ourselves again. 
Yeah, that's my goal.  I recently had a mid life crisis and changed my hair blue - I'm thinking of returning to my natural roots.

My wife would destroy me if i colored my hair blue. But going back to our natural roots is always best. Biblical roots for a strong foundation. 
Yeah, my family wasn't too happy with me - they thought I was depressed.  I also own blue shoes - thought I had the "blues"

Even the blues can be healed through the words of Jesus Christ, have faith! 
Yes, I've returned to the Church, and have been attending weekly Biblical Counseling sessions - they've helped.
column4:
بله، و با ریشه‌زدن خود در کتاب مقدس، می‌توانید ارتباط قوی خانوادگی داشته باشید!

به عنوان یک مرد متاهل، پر از مذهب هستم. کتاب مقدس کتاب مورد علاقه من است. کدام کتاب از کتاب مقدس شماست؟

بله مزامیر زیبا هستند. من و همسرم دوست داریم قبل از خواب مزامیر را بخوانیم تا آرامش بیابیم.

همه ما گمراه می‌شویم، اما با بازگشت به کتاب خوب می‌توانیم دوباره خودمان را پیدا کنیم.

همسرم من را نابود خواهد کرد اگر موهایم را آبی رنگ کنم. اما بازگشت به ریشه‌های طبیعی ما همیشه بهترین است. ریشه‌های کتاب مقدس برای یک پایه قوی.

حتی افسرده‌ترین احساسات هم می‌توانند از طریق کلمات عیسی مسیح شفا یابند، ایمان داشته باشید!
column5:
بله، مادرم برای من یک پایه قوی در کلیسا ایجاد کرد. ما به مدرسه یکشنبه و خدمات هفتگی می‌رفتیم.

مطمئن نیستم که سوال شما را متوجه شدم - اما کتاب مورد علاقه من در کتاب مقدس مزامیر است

موافقم - همیشه آرامش به من می‌آورند. خواندن به طور کلی قبل از خواب برای من این کار را انجام می‌دهد. اما اخیرا کمی از راه خدا گم شده‌ام.

بله، این هدف من است. من اخیراً برای برخورد با بحران نیمه عمر، موهایم را آبی رنگ کردم - اکنون در حال فکر کردن به بازگشت به ریشه‌های طبیعی‌ام هستم.

بله، خانواده‌ام خیلی خوشحال نبودند - فکر می‌کردند من افسرده هستم. همچنین یک جفت کفش آبی دارم - فکر کردند من افسرده هستم.

As someone who works in finance,  I can tell you we need those skilled employees!

Working in Finance has it's benefits, I'm sure you'd be a great asset ! 
"Yeah, I appreciate it - I think I'll test the waters again - I'm feeling more confident."

Do you own a car? I live walking distance from the firm and have chosen to sale mine, do you think it was a good idea? 
"If you can walk - for sure - a huge expense that you don't need.  And you get exercise to boot!"

Thanks! I thought I made the right decision. Walking does the body good! 
"Yes it does.  I actually prefer to mountain bike though.  You could always do that as a form of transportation as well.  I would if I could!"

I may try that! It would make the commute quicker even if I am close!
"Yeah - and, if you put a basket on it, you can go pick up some groceries as well."

Working in finance the hours don't give me much free time, You're absolutly right thats a great idea! 
"Yeah - anytime I can be efficient, I am.  I have kids and there's a lot that I want to do before I die - like skydive."

"Yeah, I always liked the Coldplay song Yellow.  Wasn't a huge fan of the rest of their music though."
"thats fair i also like coldplay as well as Radiohead, good english bands. And Korea Bands."

"I love Radiohead though - most of their non-radio songs.  Ok Computer was my favorite.  I used to relax and eat pizza while listening to them."
"Yeah I had Electioneering in my head all day yesterday."

"Great Song - Paranoid Android was my favorite."
"It's hard to believe the record came out almost 25 years ago. Even though I was in my 40s back then, I still loved new music."

"Yeah, a true fan can appreciate good music at all ages.  It's much like my steak preferences - I can always taste a perfectly cooked one."
"Yeah, my social security check doesn't leave much money for steak. May I come stand outside your house and sniff the air next time you cook?"

"For sure - smells are always free!"
"Do you put butter on it? I love butter because of the soft yellow shade."

"I do.  I could it with butter, and prefer mine medium to medium rare.  I actually like listening to music while I'm cooking."
"Yes, I find KPop goes well with warming up Vienna sausages"

column3:
"I would like to start going to the gym to help me lose some weight, but it's hard to get motivated? Any suggestions? "
"Hi I'm Ray. I am a physical fitness enthusiast. I believe eating healthy and exercising is a important."

"I think exorcise would really help me. What do you use to keep yourself motivated? "
"I am very conscious of my weight, so that is one motivator. Also, I feel mentally better when I exercise. That alone is motivation."

"That's a good point. I need to get on some sort of diet plan as well. I try for a few days then I get frustrated and quit."
"Setting a goal each day is helpful. Even a little exercise and at least one healthy meal each day helps alot; chicken and rice is my favorite."

"I love that idea of setting smaller daily goals. And I love chicken and rice. "
"I started going to the gym once a week, working up to 4 times a week. I also write down everything I eat. It helps to visually see the progress."

"Yeah I could see that. Kind of like banking. Keeping track of everything so I can hold myself accountable"
"Exactly! Keeping healthy food in the freezer is also good. I make my favorites (chicken and rice!) and freeze it for easy use."

"Another awesome idea! Thanks! Do you have special containers or something to freeze it?"
"I also budget like you! I use freezer ziplock bags so its easy and doesn't take much space. I let them thaw while I'm at the gym or work."

من از این ایده تعیین اهداف روزانه کوچک خیلی خوشم می آید. و من عاشق مرغ و برنج هستم.

سلام، من ری هستم. من یک علاقه‌مند به تناسب اندام هستم. من باور دارم که خوردن سالم و ورزش کردن مهم است.

من بسیار به وزن خود توجه دارم، بنابراین این یکی از انگیزه‌های من است. همچنین، حالت روحی بهتری دارم وقتی ورزش می‌کنم. این تنها خودش انگیزه است.

تعیین یک هدف هر روز مفید است. حتی انجام یک کمی تمرین و حداقل یک وعده غذای سالم هر روز بسیار کمک می‌کند؛ مرغ و برنج مورد علاقه من است.

من شروع کردم به رفتن به باشگاه ورزشی یکبار در هفته، تا اینکه به چهار بار در هفته افزایش یافت. همچنین هر چیزی که می‌خورم را نیز یادداشت می‌کنم. این کمک می‌کند تا پیشرفت را به صورت بصری مشاهده کنم.

دقیقا! نگه داشتن غذاهای سالم در فریزر هم خوب است. من غذای مورد علاقه‌ام (مرغ و برنج!) را درست می‌کنم و آن را برای استفاده آسان منجمد می‌کنم.

من هم مانند شما برنامه ریزی می کنم! من از کیسه های زیپلاک فریزر استفاده می کنم تا راحت و فضای زیادی نگیرد. من اجازه می دهم تا زمانی که در باشگاه یا محل کار هستم، آنها را بگذارم تا برود.

'Yes! Art is always a smart investment, especially since it brings so much joy! Like two for one!'
'I went to New York recently to explore my interest in becoming a museum curator.'

'Interesting!! What did you explore while you were there?'
'I visited a few museums, as well as explored the beautiful city. Do you like to travel?'

'Sounds lovely. i love to travel, but I prefer getting out of the city and into the forest. National parks are my favorite places to visit.'
'Nature is very peaceful! You can really find yourself on a visit to the national forests!'

'Absolutely! As Maxime Lagacé once said, "By discovering nature, you discover yourself".'
'Indeed. Nature is very interesting and complex to interpret. Survival is the only mechanism that drive us to have certain physical features'

'That sounds like a great premise for an Art Exhibition!'
"I enjoy watching art. Maybe I'll hapen across some of it!"

'Yes, me too. Being in nauture certainly inspires me to make art! I think thats why I go out to the woods so often. '
'i started taking painting classes recently. Outdoor art would be a fun thing to try!'

'They are 14 and 12, I hate cleaning so this should make my life a little easier! '
'Oh, poor you! But once they become full adults things will be easier!'

'True but i work a full time job in finance. So things are never that easy. '
'I,m working as a librarian full time.Also on Satuirdaymornings.'

"That's a lot of hours. Saturdays used to be my cleaning days, I hated them. "
"Oh,I don't really mind working on Sat.morning. I love talking to people."

'Working in finance all my conversations are about money, So it can be a bit boring. '
'Yes! I understand that! My conversations are not about books and writers alone. I know a lot of those people.'

"My conversations are always business related. In the finance world it's all about the Benjamin's "
'You just reminded of my favorite song of Breaking Benjamin '

'Breaking Benjamin is a great band! So Cold is a fantastic song! I can almost clean when I listen to it! '
'That is one of the tunes that is on the gold record flying out of our solar system on the Voyager probe.'

column3:
Hi! I am Mary. I have two children. My oldest son has autism. He is 7 years old and is the light of our life.
Children really give us the opportunity to see they world in a new light. You are so blessed!

Indeed! It is a blessing to have a little human that loves unconditionally. It also gives our family the opportunity to grow by serving.
Yes, I can imagine. Family is one of the most important things in the world to me! Without them, I never would have survived my terrible motorcycle accident.

Wow! You too have your challenges! No one has a perfect life. Like my son, I'm sure you deal with physical and mental therapy to cope.
Yes, My whole left knee is filled with metal. I had to learn to walk all over again. Talk about humbling..

I'm so sorry, but thankful you survived. We all do our best in life. Although my son is not "normal", he too humbles us daily.
Yes, Mary, me too! Having children with developmental disorders is so hard, and unfortunately not everyone is understanding. Blessing to you and your family.

Thankfully there are many services and therapies available to help him and us as supportive parents. The schools have also been very helpful in his progress.
That's amazing. I'll bet that some of the educational treatment works for sure. You are definitely a hero for doing this.

Awareness for autism and support for autistic adults is definitely growing. The people working for this are my heroes!
That is so true! I think social media has helped spread a lot of awareness about how widespread the disorder is.

سلام! من مری هستم. دو فرزند دارم. پسر بزرگتر من اوتیسم دار است. او ۷ ساله است و نور زندگی ماست.

به واقع! داشتن یک انسان کوچک که بطور بی قید و شرط عشق می‌ورزد، نعمتی است. این همچنین به خانواده‌مان فرصت می‌دهد تا با خدمت کردن رشد کند.

واو! شما هم چالش‌های خودتان را دارید! هیچ کس زندگی کاملی ندارد. مانند پسرم، مطمئنم که شما هم با درمان‌های جسمی و روانی برای مقابله سر و کار دارید.

متاسفم، اما سپاسگزارم که زنده ماندید. همه ما در زندگی خود بهترین خود را می‌دهیم. هر چند پسرم "عادی" نیست، او هم روزانه ما را فرو می‌برد.

با سپاس، خدمات و درمان‌های زیادی برای کمک به او و ما به عنوان والدین حامی موجود است. مدارس هم در پیشرفت او بسیار کمک کننده بوده‌اند.

آگاهی در مورد اوتیسم و حمایت از بزرگسالان اوتیست به طور قطع در حال افزایش است. افرادی که برای این کار تلاش می کنند، قهرمانان من هستند!

"It's hard enough keeping friends as an adult in the same city, but living in different places is worse. Thank goodness for social media!"

'Yess!!!!! 30 years ago, you had to call people or write them, waiting for an answer letter a couple of days.'

"I remember when internet phone services came out and they were sooo crappy! But it was the only way I could call my bf at the time"

column3:
"I'll have to. I can't haul vegetables from my garden without it! "
"I understand. Sometimes I fix also myself my car to save some money."

"Doing it yourself is always good. I grow my own herbs and vegetables for that very same reason ! "
"I like to grow my own food as well..  Fresh is the best!"

"My favorite food is raw onion. So fresh is the only option! "
"Raw onion is so good.  Raw garlic too if you can take the heat.  And raw garlic is an antibiotic.  Very good for you."

"I enjoy growing all different kinds of herbs ! Garlic is a favorite of mine as well! "
"Do you like chilis as well? I love all spicy food.  Chilis are easy to grow."

"I love chilis! You can't make a good soup without them ! Do you enjoy bell peppers? There another favorite! "
"I eat them every day.  That is how I get my vitamin C.   Great for soups or salsa but I usually eat them raw."

"They're good raw as well, just like onions! "
"Great minds think alike!"
column4:
من باید این کار را انجام دهم. نمی‌توانم سبزیجات از باغم بدون آن بکشم!

انجام دادن آن خودتان همیشه خوب است. من برای همین دلیل اعشاب و سبزیجات خود را پرورش می دهم!

غذای مورد علاقه من پیاز تازه است. تازگی تنها گزینه است!

من از کشتن انواع مختلف گیاهان دارویی لذت می‌برم! سیر هم یکی از مورد علاقه‌های من است!

من فلفل‌ها را دوست دارم! نمی‌توانی یک سوپ خوب بدون آن‌ها درست کنی! آیا از فلفل‌های دلمه‌ای لذت می‌بری؟ آن‌ها هم یکی از مورد علاقه‌های من هستند!

آن‌ها هم خام خوبند، مانند پیاز!

من هم دوست دارم غذای خودم را بردارم.. تازه بهترین است!

پیاز تازه خیلی خوب است. سیر تازه هم اگر تحمل حرارتش را داشته باشید، خوب است. و سیر تازه یک آنتی بیوتیک است. برای شما خیلی خوب است.

آیا شما هم به فلفل‌ها علاقه دارید؟ من عاشق تمام غذاهای تند هستم. رشد فلفل‌ها آسان است.

هر روز آن‌ها را می‌خورم. اینجاست که ویتامین C خود را می‌گیرم. عالی برای سوپ یا سالسا اما من معمولاً آن‌ها را خام می‌خورم.

ذهن‌های بزرگ به یکسان فکر می‌کنند!
